Probabilistic Methods, Case Based

Explanation: 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper mentions the use of "statistical and probabilistic techniques" in combination with temporal abstractions to analyze the data from home monitoring of diabetic patients. This indicates the use of probabilistic methods in the pre-processing and analysis of the data.

Case Based: The paper also describes how Intelligent Data Analysis methods may be used to index past cases and perform a case-based retrieval in a database of past cases. This indicates the use of case-based reasoning in the analysis of the data.
